We iterate through the string once to check for mismatches between adjacent characters. If a mismatch is found, we decrement the minimum number of turns needed. Since we only need to check each character once, the time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the string. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the variable `minTurns`. There are no energy implications in this problem, as it only involves simple string manipulation and does not involve any resource-intensive operations.

